ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I learned a lot in a very short time. I would definitely recommend it.
I'm not sure if the things I believe about the language are actually intrinsic to the language or not. With that in mind I would not recommendit to another student.
Yes, this is an excellent course to take, particularly if you already have some familiarity with Aramaic or Late Biblical Hebrew.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I feel prepared to take my departmental Aramaic exam after this course.
I worked extremely hard in this class. It has my blood, sweat, and tears all over it. While I don't regret having taken this course, I hope that I never again have to take a class like this.
